ndle\\\" : \\\"javax.servlet.http.LocalStrings\\\"\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777808079219}]}\n4839:[thinking] **Considering reflection and metadata**\n4841:[thinking] I’m thinking about how direct reflection in native code requires metadata at build time if the agent configuration is used. That seems good, as the test has reflection linked to the ResolverConfig's private method. There might be extra tracking for library classes, but it shouldn’t be an issue. I also need to temporarily clear dns.server/search, but I’ll remember to restore the system properties and locale afterwards with a helper using try/finally.\n4845:[thinking] I’m figuring out that the test task likely relies on metadata. Without it for the sun, the native ResolverConfig.findSunJVM might misfire. I think that to directly findWin for getBundle, the metadata for the bundle will be essential at runtime. The agent config could come into play if there's a nativeTest following the test. The instructions I read suggest that tests should typically run under Native Image by default, which seems to indicate a nativeTest in the workflow after javaTest.\n4847:[thinking] **Exploring metadata options**\n4849:[thinking] I’m considering if I could add manual metadata reflection for a private method or field. Would that broaden the usability? It seems that this would only apply to the active class. I need to verify if we have the correct metadata syntax. This involves searching through the method entries to see what’s possible. There’s definitely some complexity here, but it could lead to improved functionality!\n4853:[tool-call] delta {\"path\":\"metadata/commons-codec/commons-codec/1.10/reachability-metadata.json\",\"limit\":80}\n4854:[tool-call] end id=call_AnR1I8cNPaQy5NIGITkDOyTm|fc_0daabe48e56945910169f732eec76c81a287c3c3c005d54cdf name=read args={\"path\": \"metadata/commons-codec/commons-codec/1.10/reachability-metadata.json\", \"limit\": 80}\n4855:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Creating resource files**\\n\\nI'm needing to create resource files in the test resources, specifically for org/xbill/DNS/windows/DNSServer.properties, which includes defaults and an _en version. The code will first get the bundle with no locale, defaulting to en_US. The ResourceBundle will try variations before settling on the base. I need to ensure that the keys and values match the labels in a fake ipconfig while parsing tokenized inputs correctly. These will include host names and DNS servers.\\n\\n**Testing resource bundle functionality**\\n\\nI'm working on the line where the last token is 192.0.2.53, with a continuation line for the next server, 192.0.2.54. I need to confirm that readingServers is true and that the absence of a colon requires adding it. I want to test the default getBundle along with a locale overload. The private method findWin should check both overloads to ensure that if servers are null, I reset and check with a blank locale too. This leads to complex parsing scenarios, especially regarding the default locale. Setting Locale.setDefault(Locale.US) during the test should help me get the appropriate resource bundle.\\n\\n**Creating mismatched keys**\\n\\nI'm setting up keys for the en_US labels to deliberately not match for testing purposes. If servers are null, I intend to reset and call findWin with a new Locale of (\\\"\\\", \\\"\\\"). This should ideally pick up the base properties to ensure proper matching. I’m also considering what happens if we need to fallback to a base – that’s important to confirm the behavior of the resource bundle under these conditions. I need to ensure everything functions as expected!\\n\\n**Considering reflection and metadata**\\n\\nI’m thinking about how direct reflection in native code requires metadata at build time if the agent configuration is used. That seems good, as the test has reflection linked to the ResolverConfig's private method. There might be extra tracking for library classes, but it shouldn’t be an issue. I also need to temporarily clear dns.server/search, but I’ll remember to restore the system properties and locale afterwards with a helper using try/finally.\\n\\n**Evaluating test task setup**\\n\\nI’m figuring out that the test task likely relies on metadata. Without it for the sun, the native ResolverConfig.findSunJVM might misfire. I think that to directly findWin for getBundle, the metadata for the bundle will be essential at runtime. The agent config could come into play if there's a nativeTest following the test. The instructions I read suggest that tests should typically run under Native Image by default, which seems to indicate a nativeTest in the workflow after javaTest.\\n\\n**Exploring metadata options**\\n\\nI’m considering if I could add manual metadata reflection for a private method or field. Would that broaden the usability? It seems that this would only apply to the active class. I need to verify if we have the correct metadata syntax. This involves searching through the method entries to see what’s possible. There’s definitely some complexity here, but it could lead to improved functionality!\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0daabe48e56945910169f732d5366081a29914c293bfa40944\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp9zLuNe81JxclT1cPTfAkq2CvpwTxKplpi3n3rV5I9BR8nhecSzem9WryEDNVzy7C7Is6Sl0-sAxzeQC9DVyVIZkhwIvD915lvWcGliwAcfhEq9e3T0DX_xyyW3GBsviXxYU8V6vVdOopTFOE9pS_Bsf2LUQdY49oyqzT0-HM301wcBVRBkvaw5KO8g4zugNPQ-4WjmUfFVI5Ule1swqigaAUieAO3gPACT3YXM32Zaip-Zc2YDjzj2R_WJ4crpi78f1lyQfsKznO5F12Y3vEAKk-7zbzm7lBv6fVkKVa1wrU_Iejcox4rmK8sMU8E77NLV2AG7u8TiUuPsFZSsu9bn6qWNojjEVGqx4_ujK_m1AW_KLsNChAOA9I4_Q00Y9GSGPtIxPq0DrG0Rn2er7sb44eaozLPBjolaa8jkHPpLHCD9dRFinlg_RNuoEl6vRBDwLrvq8T3VzQg0n-NPITFs50cAaJkaD2PxaqYCPp47ozgz4RPW0Rx24o4ByVWBrlkBL_QhhKwawzzkO47PtHB4GqFYfa9ZT4aer0iyQIfXdmwr8L4ftHwb5PDIPb-wW