ip leading indentation and could cause parsing issues.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering ResourceBundle fallback behavior**\\\\n\\\\nI'm looking into the Java ResourceBundle.Control fallback locale. The method getFallbackLocale returns the default locale when the target locale isn’t the default. For a Locale with empty parameters, it might revert to Locale.US, which suggests it could end up picking en_US again instead of the base. The ResourceBundle algorithm indicates that the candidate locales start with [root], and if no bundle is found, it defaults back to Locale.getDefault. However, if base is found, it shouldn't need to fallback, but en_US might still be cached from a previous request.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_Y1C2zhA1MPipAUU6urrHAA1m|fc_0daabe48e56945910169f73322a0b481a2ae40dc1d61ebd1e6\", \"name\": \"read\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/dnsjava/dnsjava/2.1.7/build.gradle\"}}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_IKJA9L7aXca8ljL2C6A3EH1L|fc_0daabe48e56945910169f73322a0cc81a2aa46820724211bf0\", \"name\": \"read\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/dnsjava/dnsjava/2.1.7/src/test/java/dnsjava/dnsjava/ResolverConfigTest.java\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 682, \"output\": 970, \"cacheRead\": 56832, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 58484, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777808147914, \"responseId\": \"resp_0daabe48e56945910169f73314829481a28c836693031f05a2\"}, \"toolResults\": [{\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_Y1C2zhA1MPipAUU6urrHAA1m|fc_0daabe48e56945910169f73322a0b481a2ae40dc1d61ebd1e6\", \"toolName\": \"read\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this